Financing Business:
   Greyhound Lines Inc.
Greyhound said net proceeds from the new offering will be
used to repay in full the company's $55.7 million secured
term loan, increase insurance deposits and reduce or repay in
full a $22.7 million promissory note owed to Dial Corp. Any
remaining net proceeds will be used for general corporate
purposes and may be applied to repay certain other senior
debt or to make capital expenditures, the company said.
   The company said that, to complete the offering, it must
modify its existing credit agreement and obtain consents from
certain creditors. Smith Barney, Harris Upham  Co. will be
the sole underwriter.